arch:property.oc:show_val: This is a moderate size unit of mostly sheep-size with a little large mammal. Fairly fragmented, surfaces not fresh but not very worn. Very little burning or digestion. All body zones represented, but very light on vertebrae, heavy on long bone shafts and ribs. Diagnostics all sheep/goat. One bird specimen, one bone tool fragment. Looks like a slowish accumulation, but not particularly reworked: small bit of midden. Sample 1 >4mm flotation, 100% sorted, recorded for diagnostics and flot frags only. It is a large sample, in fact slightly larger than the dry-sieved. It has slightly more burning and rather more digestion, especially in the phalanges. Under-representation of vertebrae less pronounced. Most diagnostics are sheep/goat, but also a female pig maxilla (and a small fragment of male pig upper canine). Four specimens of fish and one of microfauna; striking that there is no bird from a sample this size. Looks very middeny.
